[src:diesel-orm-rust/type-safety] When the program runs it will output a garbage floating-point value.
[src:diesel-orm-rust/type-safety] The two child classes have members of different types.
[src:diesel-orm-rust/type-safety] When downcasting a parent class pointer to a child class pointer, then the resulting pointer may not point to a valid object of correct type.
[src:diesel-orm-rust/type-safety] In the example, this leads to garbage value being printed.
